Today I went off auditing some other masters thesis defense proceedings
and dang they shredded some people
This is exactly what the defense was like
these guys were hitting those dudes hard
One dude was challenged that his code won’t compile because function prototype was missing
Isn't that something you should know when writing in a language?
You guys won’t understand the more complex ones :smile:
As long as it's not beyond this earth
One of them was asked why the NOP column from his generated testability circuit randomly generated test pattern seed was marked as redundant despite it being included in the table
You can't create a branch called `feature/#2` because that #2 is a comment, right?
you basically have an 12 column table of 8bit seed values
So the question was very relevant…
I don't get what you mean with NOP *column*. I know what a NOP 'command' is in assembly, but what do you mean with a column <@U08GFT5V5>?
if you want to test this you do something like A 0 and B 0 check OUT right?
so I can create a table of patterns out like this to test OUT
it gets more complicated the bigger the circuit
and ultimately an NP complete problem
so the tests you need to run become to many to run in finite time
Oh I once learned about NP...
most people hard code a subset of the tests, that are statistically more likely to occur
that’s the kind of test your CPU does in POST to make sure it’s not broken
his thesis was a test, to test the test
So you feed it an 8bit test pattern 01101011 -> NOP negates it to 00000000
that’s why it’s seemingly redundant but still statistically relevant
What marked it as redundant? Some software he wrote?
So he was wrong marking it as redundant?
He was challenged on that point
small statement in his 90 page thesis
So he was saying it was redundant but the jurors disagreed?
Well he was challenged on that point
doesn’t mean they necessarily think he’s wrong, just challenging his work
I want to know why he thinks it's redundant
if you are unable to defend or substantiate your claim, you loose credibility
Less credibility means less confidence in your work = lower grade
if you made a mistake, prepare to be ripped to shreds
One guy today had his thesis destroyed by the reviewer
backbone formula of his work had issues
domino effect over the rest of the paper
Yeah, because during the defense you start to see the problem
once it clicked in the dudes head, he had no words
He must've been like "Well I'm fucked"
And that was only after the first 6 questions
just dragging the guy in the dirt
I feel bad for the guy
And the guy’s main supervisor was absent to attend some conference
No one to ultimately speak up for the guy
There was this other guy who did a defense on implementing a neural network in hardware
but there was the one guy in the committee who found the 1 flaw in the paper
He kept hitting on the guys work, going deeper and deeper and deeper
comparing the software implementation to hardware implementation
Well null comparison actually. The conditions weren’t necessarily the same
There is a formula that the network uses that can’t be implemented in hardware
so software runs the numbers and ends up with approximation
he basically brute forced it and turned it into a table which is valid
comparing the performance afterwards showed that his hardware used less clock cycles than software
he forgot that the software still had to do the math
big gaping hole in the work, so they basically capitalized on that
Started digging to find more problems
how are they after the grilling?

attachments.text: We've given DB Navigator a totally new look. Your personal travel planner now has the following great features. Your travel planner. All the details of your journey are available at a single glance, such as timely notification of your upcoming train transfers, connections, station information, alternative routes and delay notices. Your favourites. It's now so easy to travel to your favourite getaways. Just save the destinations that you love to visit, along with connections and train times. Even better - Faster information in the event of disruptions. DB Navigator has a direct link to Live Auskunft in its menu and factors in train cancellations and real-time data when searching for connections. Map. You can see not only your exact location, but also all nearby stops (including local public transport like bus und subway), station information, and even carsharing Flinkster and Call a Bike hiring points for ease of planning. Buy regional tickets via the app. DB Navigator's menu now includes a link to our ever popular regional travel offers: Länder-Tickets, the Schönes-Wochenende-Ticket and the Quer-Durchs-Land-Ticket. All for instant mobile reservation! Super-fast ticket access. You can now access your ticket straight from the app's home page on the day of travel. Save money while you travel. The saver fare finder shows you the cheapest ticket for the route you want to take. Delay alarm. Set up a delay alarm before you travel and you'll be kept up to date with the latest developments via e-mail or push notifications. Ideal for commuters: select duration and days as you require. Have fun exploring these great new features, and enjoy your trip. We'd love to hear from you. Simply use the in-app contact function to provide us with your feedback.
